&lt;/p&gt;


&lt;p class=&quot;jp&quot;&gt;    
  祇園・建仁寺の砂庭と遊歩道のごく一部。
&lt;/p&gt;</content><author><name>Daniel Sofer</name></author><category term="Kyoto" /><category term="Temples" /><category term="Gardens" /><category term="Architecture" /><summary type="html">Small portion of the sand garden and walkway at Kennin-ji temple in Gion.</summary><media:thumbnail xmlns:media="http://search.yahoo.com/mrss/" url="https://hermosawavephotography.com/assets/images/2022/2204_IMG_5288.jpg" /><media:content medium="image" url="https://hermosawavephotography.com/assets/images/2022/2204_IMG_5288.jpg" xmlns:media="http://search.yahoo.com/mrss/" /></entry><entry><title type="html">Nagaoka Tenmangu・長岡天満宮</title><link href="https://hermosawavephotography.com/220420/" rel="alternate" type="text/html" title="Nagaoka Tenmangu・長岡天満宮" /><published>2022-04-20T00:00:00+09:00</published><updated>2022-04-20T00:00:00+09:00</updated><id>https://hermosawavephotography.com/nagaoka</id><content type="html" xml:base="https://hermosawavephotography.com/220420/">&lt;p class=&quot;en&quot;&gt;
  Spring in Kyoto, as in many other places around the world, is marked by  flowers blooming, one after another. First plum blossoms, then cherry blossoms; followed by azaleas, wisterias, and so on. So that is how we come to Nagaoka Tenmangu shrine, where red kirishima azaleas are in bloom. 
&lt;/p&gt;


&lt;p class=&quot;jp&quot;&gt;    
  京都の春は、花々が次々と咲き誇る季節です。梅、桜、それからつつじ、藤......。そんなわけで、霧島つづじの咲く今日は長岡天満宮にやってきました。
&lt;/p&gt;</content><author><name>Daniel Sofer</name></author><category term="Kyoto" /><category term="Shrines" /><category term="Flowers" /><summary type="html">Spring in Kyoto, as in many other places around the world, is marked by flowers blooming, one after another. First plum blossoms, then cherry blossoms; followed by azaleas, wisterias, and so on. So that is how we come to Nagaoka Tenmangu shrine, where red kirishima azaleas are in bloom.</summary><media:thumbnail xmlns:media="http://search.yahoo.com/mrss/" url="https://hermosawavephotography.com/assets/images/2022/2204_A7R07737.jpg" /><media:content medium="image" url="https://hermosawavephotography.com/assets/images/2022/2204_A7R07737.jpg" xmlns:media="http://search.yahoo.com/mrss/" /></entry><entry><title type="html">Karesansui・枯山水</title><link href="https://hermosawavephotography.com/220419/" rel="alternate" type="text/html" title="Karesansui・枯山水" /><published>2022-04-19T00:00:00+09:00</published><updated>2022-04-19T00:00:00+09:00</updated><id>https://hermosawavephotography.com/ryoanji</id><content type="html" xml:base="https://hermosawavephotography.com/220419/">&lt;p class=&quot;en&quot;&gt;
  Morning at Ryoanji Temple, where the maple trees have filled out into a lush green. This is the stone garden (karesansui); a quiet morning for contemplation.
&lt;/p&gt;


&lt;p class=&quot;jp&quot;&gt;    
朝の龍安寺の石庭（枯山水）は、もみじの若葉の鮮やかな緑に包まれています。瞑想のための静かな朝。
&lt;/p&gt;</content><author><name>Daniel Sofer</name></author><category term="Kyoto" /><category term="Temples" /><category term="Gardens" /><summary type="html">Morning at Ryoanji Temple, where the maple trees have filled out into a lush green. This is the stone garden (karesansui); a quiet morning for contemplation.</summary><media:thumbnail xmlns:media="http://search.yahoo.com/mrss/" url="https://hermosawavephotography.com/assets/images/2022/2204_A7R07636.jpg" /><media:content medium="image" url="https://hermosawavephotography.com/assets/images/2022/2204_A7R07636.jpg" xmlns:media="http://search.yahoo.com/mrss/" /></entry><entry><title type="html">Shinsenen・神泉苑</title><link href="https://hermosawavephotography.com/220418/" rel="alternate" type="text/html" title="Shinsenen・神泉苑" /><published>2022-04-18T00:00:00+09:00</published><updated>2022-04-18T00:00:00+09:00</updated><id>https://hermosawavephotography.com/shinsenen</id><content type="html" xml:base="https://hermosawavephotography.com/220418/">&lt;p class=&quot;en&quot;&gt;
