   Looking through teller windows at the Museum of Kyoto Annex. The Annex was originally the Bank of Japan - Kyoto, built in 1906, and these are the windows where customers would make their transactions. It is now an exhibit space, used for the &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.kyotographie.jp/en/&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;Kyotographie International Photography Festival&lt;/a&gt;, going on this month.
&lt;/p&gt;


&lt;p class=&quot;jp&quot;&gt;    
 京都文化博物館別館で窓越しに見る。別館は1906年に建てられた日本銀行京都支店が前身で、この窓口がお客さんの取引窓口になっていました。現在は展示スペースになっており、今月開催される「&lt;a href=&quot;https://www.kyotographie.jp/&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;Kyotographie 国際写真祭&lt;/a&gt;」でも使用されている。
&lt;/p&gt;</content><author><name>Daniel Sofer</name></author><category term="Kyoto" /><category term="Architecture" /><summary type="html">Looking through teller windows at the Museum of Kyoto Annex. The Annex was originally the Bank of Japan - Kyoto, built in 1906, and these are the windows where customers would make their transactions. It is now an exhibit space, used for the Kyotographie International Photography Festival, going on this month.</summary><media:thumbnail xmlns:media="http://search.yahoo.com/mrss/" url="https://hermosawavephotography.com/assets/images/2022/2204_A7R07538.jpg" /><media:content medium="image" url="https://hermosawavephotography.com/assets/images/2022/2204_A7R07538.jpg" xmlns:media="http://search.yahoo.com/mrss/" /></entry><entry><title type="html">Omuro Ninnaji・御室仁和寺</title><link href="https://hermosawavephotography.com/220412/" rel="alternate" type="text/html" title="Omuro Ninnaji・御室仁和寺" /><published>2022-04-12T00:00:00+09:00</published><updated>2022-04-12T00:00:00+09:00</updated><id>https://hermosawavephotography.com/ninnaji</id><content type="html" xml:base="https://hermosawavephotography.com/220412/">&lt;p class=&quot;en&quot;&gt;
   The Omuro Zakura Garden at Ninnaji temple. As the cherry blossoms fall to the ground and new leaves sprout, we are reaching the end of sakura season in Kyoto.
&lt;/p&gt;


&lt;p class=&quot;jp&quot;&gt;    
   仁和寺の御室桜の庭。桜が散り、新緑が芽吹く頃、京都の桜の季節も終わりを告げようとしています。
&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;div class=&quot;subimagegroup&quot;&gt;
   &lt;img src=&quot;/assets/images/2022/2204_A7R07520.jpg&quot;/&gt;   
&lt;/div&gt;</content><author><name>Daniel Sofer</name></author><category term="Kyoto" /><category term="Cherry Blossoms" /><category term="Temples" /><summary type="html">The Omuro Zakura Garden at Ninnaji temple. As the cherry blossoms fall to the ground and new leaves sprout, we are reaching the end of sakura season in Kyoto.</summary><media:thumbnail xmlns:media="http://search.yahoo.com/mrss/" url="https://hermosawavephotography.com/assets/images/2022/2204_A7R07528.jpg" /><media:content medium="image" url="https://hermosawavephotography.com/assets/images/2022/2204_A7R07528.jpg" xmlns:media="http://search.yahoo.com/mrss/" /></entry><entry><title type="html">Hikone Castle・彦根城</title><link href="https://hermosawavephotography.com/220411/" rel="alternate" type="text/html" title="Hikone Castle・彦根城" /><published>2022-04-11T00:00:00+09:00</published><updated>2022-04-11T00:00:00+09:00</updated><id>https://hermosawavephotography.com/hikone-castle</id><content type="html" xml:base="https://hermosawavephotography.com/220411/">&lt;p class=&quot;en&quot;&gt;
   Hikone Castle in the evening. Located east of Kyoto in Shiga Prefecture, &lt;a href=&quot;https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Hikone_Castle&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;Hikone Castle&lt;/a&gt; is one of only 12 original castles in Japan (the others are modern reconstructions).
&lt;/p&gt;


&lt;p class=&quot;jp&quot;&gt;    
    夜の彦根城。京都の東、滋賀県にある&lt;a href=&quot;https://ja.wikipedia.org/wiki/%E5%BD%A6%E6%A0%B9%E5%9F%8E&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;彦根城&lt;/a&gt;は、日本に12しかないオリジナルの城の一つです（他は近代的な復元）。
&lt;/p&gt;
